Ahh, so maybe it is because you're not using the filter widget. Actually, more precisely, it is because the `filterStart` event isn't being triggered so the pager [`pageReset` option](http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/index.html#pager-page-reset) is never checked, nor updated.

What you're going to have to do is modify the `customAjaxUrl` function:

```js
customAjaxUrl: function(table, url) {
  $('tbody').html('Loading...');
  var params = prepareRequestParams();
  url = url.replace( '&page=' + table.config.pager.page + '&', '&page=0&' ) + '&' + params;
  // $(table).trigger('changingUrl', url); // are you using this code?
  return url;
},
```

I commented out the `changeUrl` trigger because that was added as an example to show that other stuff can be done in the callback. Remove it, unless you really are using it for something.

