nice example. Maybe it would be cleaner as a class with a ``__call__`` though:
```python
class grouped_color_func(object):
    def __init__(self, word_to_color, default="white"):
        self.word_to_color = word_to_color
        self.default = default
    def __call__(self, word, **kwargs):
        if word in self.word_to_color:
            return self.word_to_color[word]
        return self.default
````

