This kind of error typically occurs, if the number of audio frames of a sample is lower than the number of  characters of its transcription. In most cases this is due to wrong sample transcriptions. However: At least once there was also some edge case with a very fast speaker. For the Fisher data set I identified this problematic samples and either excluded them or corrected their transcriptions. We closed this bug, as this procedure is known to fix this kind of problems.
Certain network geometry settings can influence sensitivity to this effect. That could be the reason for the difference to ds2-v2. 
