I've added two more commits to this pull request: one to display the ngrok URL on startup, and one to address the refresh token error you discovered.

The refresh token error is caused by Google not handing out refresh tokens unless the user has explicitly consented to connect to the app, and by default, Google doesn't explicitly ask the user each and every time. If the user has already consented, Google remembers that consent and doesn't bother to ask again -- but then it also doesn't pass a refresh token, leading to the error you saw. The fix is to tell Google to _always_ explicitly ask, but that's not a great user experience, and most sites won't actually make the user connect more than once. I added guidance on how to enable that line of code if necessary. If you think it should always be enabled, let me know.

