@untitaker No. By not discovering the remote storage, no new/deleted collection would be found. Therefore, no 1:1 mirror of the remote storage would be possible.

My use case is pretty simple (and common I guess):
A automated cron job / script creates a 1:1 copy / mirror / read-only sync of a remote storage (the calendars of some user). This can be used by some logic to compute something (print a lit of upcoming events, calculate the time you spend in meetings, ... xD).

